nd writers and translators David Solway and Erin Mouré, this book celebrates the surprising ways hoaxes call attention to human capacities for flexibility, adaptation, and resilience in a cultural moment when radical empathy and imagination is critically needed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDeceptionzCanada. 0aHoaxeszCanada. 0aLiterary forgeries and mystifications. 0aTricksters. 0aTruthfulness and falsehood in art. 4aArt. 4aEthnography. 4aIndigenous Studies. 4aLiterary Criticism: Canadian Literature. 7aART / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh  aheteronym, trick, deception, art hoax, translation, haptic, haptic conceptual art, The Grange, Iris Haussler, Brian Jungen, Jeff Wall, Rebecca Belmore, Erin Moure, David Solway, Fernando Pessoa, Paul Kane, artist, curation, curator, Anthropology, Ethnography, indigenous art, settler.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112366240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771123662423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771123662/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles